Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing technologies to handle unconstrained spoken instructions.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a system for robots to understand and execute spoken instructions.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper integrates deep-learning-based object detection to handle spoken instructions.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as the paper uses object detection to identify objects in the environment.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper uses deep learning techniques for object detection and natural language processing.
